        <abstract> 
<p>Discusses foliation and cleavage. Comments on dip of cleavage laminae in mountains. Mentions views of Sedgwick and Studer. Suggests reading C. L. von Buch [<hi rend="italic">Travels through Norway and Lapland</hi> (1813)] "as an amusement". Praises views of William Hopkins. Suggests reading paper by H. D. Rogers ["On cleavage of slate-strata", <hi rend="italic">Edinburgh New Philos. J.</hi> 41 (1846): 422–3)]. Comments on the paper.</p> 
        </abstract>
